00:24:38,040 --> 00:24:42,240
3 hours later l get
a message back, saying:

265
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:44,710
''What an amazing coincidence!

266
00:24:44,710 --> 00:24:48,040
''l was going
to suggest the same thing!''

267
00:25:59,950 --> 00:26:03,480
- ls this the late edition?
- Yes, sir.

268
00:27:17,150 --> 00:27:18,710
Seen my key?

269
00:27:18,710 --> 00:27:21,870
You must've left it in the door.

270
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:27,870
Oh, no!

271
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:32,840
What are you doing here?

272
00:27:32,840 --> 00:27:35,600
The Claridge was booked solid.

273
00:27:35,600 --> 00:27:39,480
So l came here.
l took the key downstairs.

274
00:27:39,480 --> 00:27:43,390
There are other places
than the Claridge.

275
00:27:43,390 --> 00:27:48,150
- l always stay at the Claridge.
- You're crazy!

276
00:27:48,150 --> 00:27:51,600
Quit pulling a long face!

277
00:27:51,600 --> 00:27:53,350
lt doesn't suit you.

278
00:27:55,630 --> 00:27:59,430
- ''Pulling a long face''?
- Doing like this!

279
00:28:05,240 --> 00:28:07,350
lt suits me fine.

280
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:10,150
You're even crazier than me.

281
00:28:10,150 --> 00:28:11,520
What a pain.

282
00:28:13,190 --> 00:28:17,110
l always fall for girls
who aren't cut out for me.

283
00:28:17,110 --> 00:28:21,240
Did you notice
l followed you last night?

284
00:28:23,710 --> 00:28:25,240
What's wrong?

285
00:28:25,240 --> 00:28:27,950
Leave me alone. l'm thinking.

286
00:28:28,910 --> 00:28:30,280
What about?

287
00:28:32,080 --> 00:28:35,600
The thing is, l don't even know.

288
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:37,110
Well, l do.

289
00:28:37,110 --> 00:28:39,480
No, nobody does.

290
00:28:39,480 --> 00:28:42,870
You're thinking about last night.
Yes, you are.

291
00:28:42,870 --> 00:28:48,000
Last night l was furious,
but now l couldn't care less.

292
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:50,760
l'm not thinking about anything.

293
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:59,190
l'd like to think about something,
but l can't seem to.

294
00:28:59,190 --> 00:29:03,150
Well, l'm tired, very tired,

295
00:29:03,150 --> 00:29:06,080
and l'm going back to sleep.

296
00:29:11,560 --> 00:29:15,840
- Why're you looking at me?
- Because l am.

297
00:29:15,840 --> 00:29:19,350
- You should've stayed last night.
- l couldn't.

298
00:29:19,350 --> 00:29:23,630
You should've told the chap
you couldn't see him.

299
00:29:23,630 --> 00:29:26,430
l had to.
He's getting me articles to write.

300
00:29:26,430 --> 00:29:29,110
lt's really important for me.

301
00:29:29,110 --> 00:29:32,150
No, what's important
is going to Rome with me.

302
00:29:32,150 --> 00:29:35,600
Maybe, l don't know.

303
00:29:35,600 --> 00:29:37,950
Did you sleep with him?

304
00:29:39,320 --> 00:29:40,840
l bet you did.

305
00:29:40,840 --> 00:29:43,630
No. He's really sweet.

306
00:29:43,630 --> 00:29:47,390
He said one day we'd sleep together
but not now.

307
00:29:47,390 --> 00:29:49,760
But he doesn't even know me.

308
00:29:49,760 --> 00:29:52,710
Not you... Him and me.

309
00:29:52,710 --> 00:29:55,560
We had a drink in Montparnasse.

310
00:29:55,560 --> 00:29:59,080
l was there, too. At what time?

311
00:29:59,080 --> 00:30:03,110
l don't know. We didn't stay long.

312
00:30:03,110 --> 00:30:06,870
Why'd you come here, Michel?

313
00:30:06,870 --> 00:30:09,950
Because l want to sleep
with you again.

314
00:30:09,950 --> 00:30:13,600
That's hardly a reason.

315
00:30:13,600 --> 00:30:15,710
Sure, it is. lt means l love you.

316
00:30:15,710 --> 00:30:19,190
But l don't know if l love you yet.

317
00:30:20,350 --> 00:30:22,150
When will you know?

318
00:30:22,150 --> 00:30:24,350
Soon.

319
00:30:24,350 --> 00:30:28,000
What do you mean: ''soon''?
ln a month, in a year?

320
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:31,040
Soon means soon.

321
00:30:31,040 --> 00:30:33,600
A woman never wants to do
in 8 seconds

322
00:30:33,600 --> 00:30:37,240
what she'll want to do
8 days later.

323
00:30:37,240 --> 00:30:40,670
8 seconds or 8 days, it's all the same.

324
00:30:40,670 --> 00:30:43,430
Why not 8 centuries?

325
00:30:43,430 --> 00:30:46,000
No, 8 days is good.

326
00:30:47,150 --> 00:30:50,240
A woman's all half-measures.

327
00:30:50,240 --> 00:30:52,870
lt gets me down.

328
00:30:54,950 --> 00:30:57,150
Why won't you sleep with me again?

329
00:30:57,150 --> 00:30:59,800
Because l'm trying to find out

330
00:30:59,800 --> 00:31:03,800
what it is that l like about you.

331
00:31:03,800 --> 00:31:07,280
l want us to be like Romeo and Juliet.

332
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:09,240
Just like a girl!

333
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:14,800
See? You said last night you couldn't
live without me, but you can.

334
00:31:14,800 --> 00:31:19,560
Romeo couldn't live without Juliet,
but you can.

335
00:31:19,560 --> 00:31:22,760
No, l can't live without you.

336
00:31:24,150 --> 00:31:27,150
Just like a man!

337
00:31:27,150 --> 00:31:29,150
Give me a smile.

338
00:31:30,190 --> 00:31:33,670
Right! l'll count to 8.

339
00:31:33,670 --> 00:31:37,950
lf by 8 you haven't smiled,
l'll strangle you.

340
00:31:39,480 --> 00:31:41,240
2...

341
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:42,870
3...

342
00:31:42,870 --> 00:31:45,150
4, 5, 6...

343
00:31:45,150 --> 00:31:46,950
7...

344
00:31:46,950 --> 00:31:48,840
7 and a half...

345
00:31:48,840 --> 00:31:51,950
7 and three quarters.

346
00:31:51,950 --> 00:31:56,110
You're such a coward
l bet you're gonna smile.

347
00:32:00,040 --> 00:32:03,080
Enough games for today.

348
00:32:05,840 --> 00:32:07,870
Too bad you're a coward.

349
00:32:07,870 --> 00:32:09,670
Why do you say that?

350
00:32:09,670 --> 00:32:11,190
You get on my nerves.

351
00:32:11,190 --> 00:32:13,240
You do, too.

352
00:32:13,240 --> 00:32:14,800
l'm not a coward.

353
00:32:14,800 --> 00:32:16,480
How do you know?

354
00:32:16,480 --> 00:32:20,670
lf a girl says she's not scared,
then can't even light her cigarette,

355
00:32:20,670 --> 00:32:23,520
it means she's scared of something.

356
00:32:23,520 --> 00:32:27,190
l don't know of what,
but she's scared.

357
00:32:28,240 --> 00:32:31,950
- Have one.
- None of those Chesterfields.

358
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:34,800
Hand me my jacket.

359
00:32:34,800 --> 00:32:37,280
- ln this one?
- Give!

360
00:32:38,950 --> 00:32:40,840
This your passport?

361
00:32:40,840 --> 00:32:43,320
No, my brother's. Mine's in the car.

362
00:32:43,320 --> 00:32:45,840
But it says Kovacs here.

363
00:32:45,840 --> 00:32:48,840
Oh, yeah?
He's not my real brother.

364
00:32:48,840 --> 00:32:53,040
My mum was divorced
by the time he was born.

365
00:33:01,520 --> 00:33:03,950
See? l'm not scared.

366
00:33:03,950 --> 00:33:07,320
- l never said you were.
- You bet, pet.

367
00:33:09,520 --> 00:33:14,870
But you wish you had said it.
And now you're angry.

368
00:33:14,870 --> 00:33:17,840
l'm not talking to you any more.

369
00:33:22,840 --> 00:33:26,040
Do you ever think about death?

370
00:33:26,040 --> 00:33:28,390
l do, all the time.

371
00:33:30,760 --> 00:33:34,670
- What?
- Say something nice.

372
00:33:34,670 --> 00:33:37,950
- Like what?
- l don't know.

373
00:33:37,950 --> 00:33:40,630
Then neither do l.

374
00:33:42,520 --> 00:33:45,150
l like your ashtray.

375
00:33:45,150 --> 00:33:47,280
lt's Swiss.

376
00:33:47,280 --> 00:33:51,190
My granddad had a Rolls-Royce.
Great car!

377
00:33:51,190 --> 00:33:54,710
Never had to raise the bonnet
in 1 5 years!

378
00:33:56,630 --> 00:33:59,350
Seen my new poster?

379
00:34:00,040 --> 00:34:02,870
Come here!

380
00:34:02,870 --> 00:34:05,430
Come here, for Christ's sake!

381
00:34:05,430 --> 00:34:09,800
lt won't do here.
Where can l put it?

382
00:34:11,760 --> 00:34:14,350
Why'd you slap me
when l looked at your legs?

383
00:34:14,350 --> 00:34:16,710
lt wasn't my legs.

384
00:34:19,080 --> 00:34:20,670
lt's exactly the same thing.

385
00:34:20,670 --> 00:34:27,270
The French always say things
are the same when they're not at all.

386
00:34:27,270 --> 00:34:29,150
l've thought of something nice.

387
00:34:29,150 --> 00:34:31,310
What?

388
00:34:31,310 --> 00:34:34,270
l want to sleep with you again

389
00:34:34,270 --> 00:34:35,880
because you're beautiful.

390
00:34:35,880 --> 00:34:37,880
l'm not.

391
00:34:37,880 --> 00:34:39,520
Then because you're ugly.

392
00:34:39,520 --> 00:34:40,880
ls it the same?

393
00:34:47,310 --> 00:34:49,560
Yeah, kid, it's the same.

394
00:34:49,560 --> 00:34:51,000
You're a liar, Michel.

395
00:34:51,000 --> 00:34:53,360
No, lying's stupid.

396
00:34:53,360 --> 00:34:56,920
lt's like at poker...
lt's better to tell the truth.

397
00:34:56,920 --> 00:35:02,110
The others think you're bluffing,
and that's how you win.

398
00:35:02,110 --> 00:35:03,480
What is it?

399
00:35:07,440 --> 00:35:10,480
l'll stare at you
until you stop staring at me.

400
00:35:10,480 --> 00:35:11,830
Me, too.

401
00:35:38,190 --> 00:35:41,480
l'll put my poster in the bathroom.

402
00:35:42,520 --> 00:35:44,670
Can l phone?

403
00:35:49,190 --> 00:35:51,560
lt's not bad here.

404
00:35:51,560 --> 00:35:53,670
Just fine.

405
00:35:58,000 --> 00:36:00,920
You like my poster?

406
00:36:00,920 --> 00:36:02,270
Not bad.

407
00:36:04,360 --> 00:36:06,880
Renoir's a really great painter.

408
00:36:06,880 --> 00:36:09,790
l said, not bad!

409
00:36:10,830 --> 00:36:13,600
Think she's prettier than me?

410
00:36:16,270 --> 00:36:21,270
When you're scared or surprised,
or both at once,

411
00:36:21,270 --> 00:36:23,040
there's a funny glint in your eyes.

412
00:36:23,040 --> 00:36:24,270
So what?

413
00:36:24,270 --> 00:36:27,920
l wanna sleep with you again,
because of that glint.

414
00:36:32,830 --> 00:36:36,230
Mind if l piss in the basin?

415
00:36:36,230 --> 00:36:38,150
Guess what l'm going to say.

416
00:36:38,150 --> 00:36:40,520
No idea.

417
00:36:40,520 --> 00:36:43,040
l'm pregnant, Michel.

418
00:36:46,830 --> 00:36:49,000
You heard me.

419
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:50,630
Whose is it? Mine?

420
00:36:50,630 --> 00:36:53,150
l think so.

421
00:36:53,150 --> 00:36:54,920
Seen a doctor?

422
00:36:54,920 --> 00:36:56,790
Yesterday.

423
00:36:56,790 --> 00:37:00,830
l have to go back Thursday
for tests.

424
00:37:00,830 --> 00:37:03,480
You should've been more careful!

425
00:37:17,310 --> 00:37:20,000
Get me ELY. 99.84.

426
00:37:26,080 --> 00:37:27,830
ls Antonio there?

427
00:37:30,230 --> 00:37:33,790
You don't know if he's coming back?

428
00:37:33,790 --> 00:37:35,830
l'll call back.

429
00:37:45,600 --> 00:37:48,400
ELY. 25.32.

430
00:37:50,670 --> 00:37:54,040
l'm calling
the man who owes me money.

431
00:37:56,080 --> 00:37:58,230
Mr. Tolmachov, please.

432
00:38:00,270 --> 00:38:02,480
Hey, sonny.

433
00:38:05,920 --> 00:38:09,040
l couldn't find Berruti.

434
00:38:10,040 --> 00:38:13,670
l wandered
around Montparnasse all night.

435
00:38:16,080 --> 00:38:17,880
The police?

436
00:38:20,630 --> 00:38:22,520
Thanks. Ciao, sonny.

437
00:38:25,400 --> 00:38:26,400
Shit!

438
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:28,520
- What?
- l slipped.

439
00:38:29,670 --> 00:38:33,440
Heard the one
about the condemned man?

440
00:38:33,440 --> 00:38:39,600
As he's climbing the scaffold,
he slips and says, ''That figures!''

441
00:38:44,630 --> 00:38:47,400
You look like a Martian up close.

442
00:38:47,400 --> 00:38:50,230
Because my head's in the clouds.

443
00:38:50,230 --> 00:38:52,360
Some idea, having a kid!

444
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:54,230
But it's not sure.

445
00:38:54,230 --> 00:38:56,480
l wanted to see what you'd say.

446
00:38:56,480 --> 00:38:59,670
- Take your clothes off.
- What's the point?

447
00:38:59,670 --> 00:39:02,960
- You Americans are so stupid.
- Why?

448
00:39:02,960 --> 00:39:06,920
You adore La Fayette
and Maurice Chevalier.

449
00:39:06,920 --> 00:39:10,440
And they're the stupidest French!

450
00:39:10,440 --> 00:39:12,630
l'm making another call.

451
00:39:14,790 --> 00:39:16,830
Belle Epine 35.26.

452
00:39:16,830 --> 00:39:19,880
Patricia, come here!

453
00:39:22,400 --> 00:39:24,480
Mr. Mansard?

454
00:39:24,480 --> 00:39:30,440
Will he be in this afternoon?
Tell him l'll come by.

455
00:39:30,440 --> 00:39:33,600
l'm a friend of Tony's. From Marseilles.

456
00:39:33,600 --> 00:39:37,190
l've got an American.

457
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:40,750
An American?

458
00:39:44,080 --> 00:39:49,520
Not you. An American car.

459
00:39:53,400 --> 00:39:58,000
l can't find the man
who owes me money. What a pain!

460
00:39:58,000 --> 00:40:00,440
Do you prefer records or the radio?

461
00:40:00,440 --> 00:40:03,520
Quiet, l'm thinking!

462
00:40:19,750 --> 00:40:22,790
l know them all.

463
00:40:22,790 --> 00:40:24,920
- How old are you?
- l'll put the radio on.

464
00:40:24,920 --> 00:40:26,960
l'm 20.

465
00:40:26,960 --> 00:40:29,880
You don't look it.

466
00:40:29,880 --> 00:40:32,110
Why don't you like music?

467
00:40:32,110 --> 00:40:34,360
lt depends. l do...

468
00:40:34,360 --> 00:40:36,830
C'mon, Patricia, come to ltaly.

469
00:40:41,150 --> 00:40:44,880
What's the point of studying
at the Sorbonne?

470
00:40:44,880 --> 00:40:48,000
You never took any exams.

471
00:40:48,000 --> 00:40:52,040
Sure, the baccalaureate.
But l packed it in.

472
00:40:52,040 --> 00:40:53,830
What's ''packed it in''?

473
00:40:53,830 --> 00:40:55,560
l did other things.

474
00:40:55,560 --> 00:40:58,190
- Like what?
- l sold cars.

475
00:40:58,190 --> 00:40:59,670
Here?

476
00:41:02,670 --> 00:41:04,040
ln New York.

477
00:41:05,080 --> 00:41:08,360
You sleep with a lot of men?

478
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:10,360
Not so many.

479
00:41:12,310 --> 00:41:13,670
How many?

480
00:41:15,960 --> 00:41:17,710
How about you?

481
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:22,670
Not so many either.

482
00:41:24,150 --> 00:41:28,110
You know where l'd like to live?
Mexico.

483
00:41:28,110 --> 00:41:30,150
l hear it's really lovely.

484
00:41:30,150 --> 00:41:34,560
When l was a kid my dad would say:
We'll go next Saturday.

485
00:41:34,560 --> 00:41:37,360
But he'd always forget.

486
00:41:39,110 --> 00:41:41,560
No, Mexico doesn't grab me.

487
00:41:41,560 --> 00:41:43,830
l bet it's not all that great.

488
00:41:43,830 --> 00:41:46,150
People are such liars.

489
00:41:46,150 --> 00:41:49,270
lt's like Stockholm. Everyone says...

490
00:41:49,270 --> 00:41:54,360
''Swedish girls are terrific.
l had 3 a day. Go there.''

491
00:41:54,360 --> 00:41:57,920
l went there. lt's not true.

492
00:41:57,920 --> 00:42:00,920
Swedish girls don't act
the way they do here.

493
00:42:00,920 --> 00:42:04,190
And most of them are dogs
like Parisian girls.

494
00:42:04,190 --> 00:42:07,920
No, Swedish girls are very pretty.

495
00:42:07,920 --> 00:42:10,880
lt's a myth.

496
00:42:10,880 --> 00:42:17,000
One or two maybe - just like in Paris
or London - but not all of them.

497
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:20,230
The cities where the girls are pretty

498
00:42:20,230 --> 00:42:24,400
- not gorgeous, but like you, charming -

499
00:42:24,400 --> 00:42:32,440
girls who rate 1 5 out of 20, because
they have a certain something...

500
00:42:32,440 --> 00:42:37,750
aren't Rome or Paris or Rio
but Lausanne and Geneva.

501
00:42:40,230 --> 00:42:42,710
You tell me something nice, too.

502
00:42:42,710 --> 00:42:45,750
l don't know what, either.

503
00:42:49,560 --> 00:42:53,880
Would you let another man caress you?

504
00:42:56,110 --> 00:43:01,960
You know, you said l'm scared.
lt's true, l'm scared.

505
00:43:01,960 --> 00:43:05,040
Because l want you to love me.

506
00:43:05,040 --> 00:43:10,400
But at the same time,
l want you to stop loving me.

507
00:43:10,400 --> 00:43:13,560
l'm very independent, you know.

508
00:43:15,920 --> 00:43:19,670
l love you, but not the way you think.

509
00:43:19,670 --> 00:43:22,790
- How then?
- Not the way you think.

510
00:43:22,790 --> 00:43:26,920
But you don't know what l think.
You don't know.

511
00:43:26,920 --> 00:43:30,400
- Sure, l do.
- But you don't.

512
00:43:30,400 --> 00:43:34,960
l want to know
what's behind your face.

513
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:41,080
l've looked at it for 1 0 minutes now,
and l still know nothing, nothing.

514
00:43:41,080 --> 00:43:44,230
l'm not sad. l'm scared.

515
00:43:45,270 --> 00:43:47,270
Sweet, gentle Patricia.

516
00:43:47,270 --> 00:43:54,270
OK, then, cruel, stupid, heartless,
pathetic, cowardly, despicable.

517
00:43:55,400 --> 00:43:59,040
You don't even how
to apply your lipstick.

518
00:43:59,040 --> 00:44:01,080
Now you're hideous.

519
00:44:01,080 --> 00:44:03,830
Say what you like, l don't care.

520
00:44:03,830 --> 00:44:06,360
l'll put all this in my book.

521
00:44:06,360 --> 00:44:09,480
- What book?
- l'm writing a novel.

522
00:44:09,480 --> 00:44:13,440
- You?
- Why not me? What are you doing?

523
00:44:13,440 --> 00:44:14,960
Taking off your top.

524
00:44:14,960 --> 00:44:16,600
Not now.

525
00:44:16,600 --> 00:44:20,830
You're a bloody pain! What is all this?

526
00:44:20,830 --> 00:44:23,710
You know William Faulkner?

527
00:44:23,710 --> 00:44:26,750
